                                                                                                                                   Kyle Mills   penalised
            A STAFF REPORTER AMP; AGENCIES                            
	Calcutta/Karachi: New Zealand bowler Kyle Mills has been fined 20 per cent of his match fee for two breaches of the ICC Code of Conduct during his teams one-day International against Pakistan in Abu Dhabi on Monday.         
	Following a hearing, which was convened by Match Referee Andy Pycroft, Mills was found guilty of two out of the three charges swearing and excessive appealing.         
	Meanwhile, the Pakistan Cricket Board officials have been summoned by both houses of the Parliament to explain the recent loss to New Zealand.                                                                                                                       
